more realistic than the typical approach of categorizing a road as
either blocked or free flowing. The framework is demonstrated on
Newcastle upon Tyne in the United Kingdom and shows that by the 2080s
disruption across the city from a 1-in-50-year event could increase by
66\%. A criticality index is developed and is shown to provide an
effective metric to prioritize intervention options in the road network.
In this case, just two adaptation interventions can reduce travel delays
across the city by 32\%.},
